@node Intro "Long live Adobe! :-)"

Nowadays PDF files have become @{b}the@{ub} standard for technical documentation.
In fact, almost every tech doc. on the web is offered in PDF...

So, what does that mean to me?

Well, you can read and print these documents using the Amiga port of the UN*X proggy GhostScript.

But, can you create such documents? 
At first you would say no, 'cause there's no Amiga version of Adobe's Acrobat...

Problems are made to be solved, so hereby I introduce the allmighty (duh...) ConvertToPDF AREXX script for creating PDF documents using FinalWriter and GhostScript!!!
Yes, that's right! @{b}Any@{ub} (well, allmost) FinalWriter document can be converted to a PDF version!

To show you it's really possible, I've included a demo PDF file (Demo.pdf) created with FinalWriter using this util.
@endnode
@node Install "How to install this thingie..."
Installation and setup:

The installation part is very, very simple.. Just copy the "Convert to PDF" file to the FinalWriter/FWMacros directory.

Setting the whole stuff up is more complicated (that is, for novices).
The AREXX script has to be called from FinalWriter itself, so you'll need to assign a command button or menu option to it.
In most cases, assigning to a menu option is sufficient.

-Select the User Preferences of FinalWriter. You'll now see an (empty) list of user menu items.
-Click the 'New' button to create a new menuitem
-Now you'll have to fill in the text that should appear in the user menu. In this case 'Convert to PDF' should be nice ;)
-You'll have to select the command type. This should be set to 'ARexx Script'.
-Press the command select button and a filerequester should appear. Now select the 'Convert to PDF' file.
-Save the settings and you're done!

@{b}NOTE:@{ub}
GhostScript has to be installed properly. This includes a GhostScript: assign.



        @{"How to use it" link Usage}
@endnode
@node Usage "So, how do I use it?"

Usage if very simple. Just load or type your FinalWriter document that has to be converted to PDF, select the Usermenu item or user button that you've @{"assigned to the script" link Install}.
After a (long if CPU<68040) while a filerequester pops up asking where to save the PDF file.
When you've named the to be created PDF file, your CPU will be very busy for a while and the PDF file will be created.

@{b}IMPORTANT NOTE@{ub}
Unless you're having lots'a RAM, it is wise to assign T: to a directory on the harddisk!
@endnode 
@node Bugware "Wanna have real buggy software? Try http://www.microsoft.com !"

Known bugs:

Actually there aren't really bugs in this script, but both FinalWriter and GhostScript have some quirks that should be noted:
Some PDF files created by this util are unreadable with any PDF reader. This is a known fault in GhostScript's PDFwrite module.
Agfa® Intellifont®s won't be included in the PDF file. This is a know bug of FinalWriter's font conversion routines. All Intellifonts will be replaced by the default font. 

